|| nov 1958 - jun 2020 ğŸ–¤ğŸ’” .
2 weken geleden hebben we oa deze foto laten maken. En gisteren hebben we al afscheid van jou moeten nemen, van de allerliefste papa en kersverse trotse opa. Het is vreselijk zo jong. We hadden nog zoveel moois mee kunnen maken. Wat me het pijnste doet is dat je Jae niet ziet opgroeien. En dit deed jou ook het meest pijn. Dit heb je geschreven in je afscheidsbrief. Wegens de huidige omstandigheden moesten we in kleine kring afscheid nemen. Alle vele vrienden, de buurt, andere familieleden enz mochten er niet bij zijn, terwijl je dit zo graag had gewild. De mensen waar je feest mee vierde moesten ook bij het afscheid zijn heb je zelf altijd gezegd. Dit is nog onbegrijpelijk en oneerlijk. Je mag wel met duizenden protesteren op de dam, en met een vliegtuig weer op vakantie. Maar een waardig afscheid met alle geliefde ho maar! Onmenselijk.. alle lieve mensen die niet bij het afscheid mochten zijn stonden met velen in de straat. Klappend jou een laatste groet geven. Wat was dit indrukwekkend en hartverwarmend. Dit bleek ook uit de 200 kaarten en 20 bloemstukken. Je was geliefd! We hebben je een waardig afscheid gegeven, en ik heb je begeleid van begin tot eind.
Voor ons gaat het nu beginnen maar dappere bikkel, jij hebt je welverdiende rust. Wij houden van jou! ğŸ–¤

Vorige week kreeg ik van een clieÌˆnt deze prachtige Amethist. Het is deÌ steen van het loslaten. Negatieve gedragspatronen en gewoontes verbreken.

En laat dit nu net een groot punt zijn waar ik mij tijdens de consulten op focus; stressreductie. Niet alleen in de vorm van mentale stress, maar (vooral) ook fysieke stress.
Weet jij eigenlijk wel wat goed voor jouw lichaam is? Heb je het gevoel dat je moeilijk kan loslaten? Ben je prikkelbaar? Heb jij veel last van hoofdpijn en/of je darmen? Voel jij je niet zo lekker in je vel?

Door langdurige stress, bijvoorbeeld door voedingsintoleranties, blijft voortdurend adrenaline en cortisol geproduceerd worden. Dit bevordert laaggradige ontstekingen, die op hun beurt weer allerlei (soms vage) klachten kunnen veroorzaken.
Langdurige stress is iets wat altijd gezondheid in de weg zit. Daarom mijn vraag aan jou? Wat maakt jou ontspannen en waar haal jij deze ontspanning uit?ğŸ™ğŸ» Deze prachtige Amethist staat vanaf nu lekker op mijn bureautje te shinen. âœ¨ Hij is (naast de helende werking) ook perfect in de kleur van Nourish to FlourishğŸ‘ŒğŸ¼ğŸ˜ğŸ’œ

post_3_content:
nourishtoflourish.nl
Misschien heb je al eens een onderzoek gedaan of weet jij dat je een zwakke darmgezondheid hebt?ğŸ¤·ğŸ¼â€â™€ï¸ Terwijl jij bezig bent je gezondheid te optimaliseren en je darm te ontzien van belasting, kan je het leuker maken dan het is; door wat gezellige poepertjes en boosters toe te voegen aan je smoothie!

De volgende ingredieÌˆnten werken o.a. ondersteunend voor de darmgezondheid en kan je makkelijk toevoegen aan je smoothies of havermoutje. Hier een paar voorbeelden:

L-glutamine is de energiebron voor snel delende cellen als ons immuunsysteem en ons darmepitheel. Kort gezegd bestaat onze darmwand uit L-glutamine en ondersteunt dit aminozuur de vorming van de zogeheten tight-junctions (houden de darmepitheel cellen bij elkaar zodat voedings deeltjes niet het darmslijmvlies in kunnen gaan). Het nemen van L-glutamine wordt dus ingezet om de darmwand sterker te maken.

Collageen is naast een belangrijke speler in het bewegingsapparaat ook onwijs belangrijk bij het versterken van de darmwand.

Quercetine is een sterke antioxidant die ontsteking tegengaat. Ontstekingsreacties zijn de grootste oorzaak van de meeste ziekten. Quercetine zit o.a. ook in appels, pepers, olijfolie, kappertjes en rode wijn (Hello FridayğŸ˜) Moringa draagt een steentje bij aan de spijsvertering door de veelzijdige werking van dit plantje. Zo gaat het ontsteking tegen, ondersteund het de lever functie, gaat hoge bloeddruk tegen, verlaagd cholesterol, helpt de schildklierfunctie te reguleren en ga zo maar door. Een mooi â€œpoedertjeâ€ om toe te voegen aan je smoothie.

Ashwaghanda is een adoptogeen en wordt binnen de ayurvedische geneeskunde al jaren gebruikt. Als adaptogeen verbetert ashwaghanda de conditie van lichaam en geest door cel veroudering tegen te gaan en heeft voornamelijk een stress verlagend effect. Waarom dit goed is voor je darmgezondheid? Omdat het helpt bij chronische en acute stress en je hierdoor jouw systeem rust geeft, waardoor er minder kans is op laaggradige ontstekingen; het immuunsysteem wordt geboost.

ğŸ•· firstly sorry to those who (like myself) are scared of spiders ğŸ•·.
.
Iâ€™d thought Iâ€™d share a couple stories of two encounters I had with these two spiders on my travels.
.
Pic 1.
The Brazilian wandering spider.
I encountered this little guy (they are massive) in Costa Rica. Whilst explaining to my friend, that the venom of these spiders is a lot worse for men. It gives you a 24hr long, incredibly painful.....erection. And after that you can lose the use of your bits forever.
On hearing those words of advice, my friend said â€œheâ€™s wandered very far from Brazilâ€.
.
Pic 2.
A golden orb web.
Now this spider is also massive, though it is harmless and makes some fantastic huge webs.
I was leading a group in Africa, when I spotted one had been hitching a ride on one of the groups rucksacks. So without alarming the poor guy with this spider on his back, I calmly grabbed a stick, then channeling my inner Steve Irwin, I slowly let the female orb web walk onto it. The group spotted my removal and took interest in the spider. As I told them a little info about the spider, trying my best to look cool. It suddenly turned and ran up the stick towards my hand! Now with what I can only describe as a squeal, I threw my stick as far as I could. To look up at my group looking a bit shocked at my reaction ğŸ•·
.
.
.
.

ğŸ¼ Die konventionelle Milchproduktion ist alles andere als natuÌˆrlich! Die Kuh wird kuÌˆnstlich besamt, nach der Geburt wird ihr das Kalb weggenommen und endet entweder als Schnitzel auf dem Teller oder ebenfalls als Milchkuh. Rund 50 Liter Milch gibt eine Milchkuh am Tag! Weil sie dauerschwanger sind, ist die Milch oft Hormon-belastet und die KuÌˆhe leiden an entzuÌˆndeten Eutern. WaÌˆhrend die natuÌˆrliche Lebenserwartung einer Kuh bei 20â€“30 Jahren liegt, wird eine Milchkuh nur maximal 4 Jahre alt.
ğŸ¼ GluÌˆckliche KuÌˆhe grasen auf gruÌˆnen Wiesen - so suggerieren es die Verpackungen von Milch, KaÌˆse, Butter und Joghurt. Die RealitaÌˆt sieht anders aus: MilchkuÌˆhe verbringen ihr Leben zusammengepfercht in Stallanlagen, viele sogar ganzjaÌˆhrig angebunden. Rund 90% aller Milcherzeugnisse stammen aus der Massentierhaltung!
ğŸ¼Diese vielen KuÌˆhe wollen ernaÌˆhrt werden, und weil das eben nicht mit saftigem Gras geht, bekommen sie Soja beigefuÌˆttert, importiert aus SuÌˆdamerika. Bei der Verdauung stoÃŸen sie Methan aus, was sich nicht gerade positiv auf die Klimabilanz auswirkt.
ğŸ¼ Auch auf unsere Gesundheit kann sich der Milchkonsum auswirken: Das in Zusammenhang mit Milch gefeierte Calcium, liefern auch zahlreiche pflanzliche Quellen, wie bspw. BlattgemuÌˆse. Zudem enthaÌˆlt Milch nur wenig Magnesium, was fuÌˆr die Knochengesundheit mindestens genauso wichtig ist. Der Verzicht auf Milchprodukte kann sich positiv auf Haut- und Darmgesundheit auswirken. UÌˆbrigens leidet rund 1/4 der WeltbevoÌˆlkerung an Laktoseintoleranz, nicht zuletzt, weil die Natur Kuhmilch nicht fuÌˆr den Menschen vorgesehen hat, sondern fuÌˆr das Kalb.

Black lives matter. How people still question the existence of racism or want to debate it frustrates me, and I can only imagine how frustrating this must be for black people who actually have experienced racism. I truly hope all these protests help us to get to a next chapter in history where we listen, learn and acknowledge all things about injustice, racism and institutional racism and create change.
I took a step away from posting my own stuff the last 10 days and just shared Insta stories around anti-racisme. I will be posting â€˜normalâ€™ posts again, but this does not mean I will stay silent on this topic. I made a promise to myself to;
- Keep reading, listing, talking and educating myself on this topic
- Challenge myself on how I can push towards more equality in my field of work
- Speak up. I will speak up when I hear somebody say racist things. I will make my voice count through signing petitions. I will show up at protests for this cause.
I truly believe in dialogue, ask questions and dare to listen - also when itâ€™s tough.
Letâ€™s get comfortable with being uncomfortable.
Love to share my favourite Robin Sharma quote here â€˜Change is hard at first, messy in the middle and gorgeous at the endâ€™

bio: Voor een groenere samenleving!â™»ï¸
post_1_content:
keukenbewust.nl
Bereikt de aarde langzamerhand een breekpunt â‰ï¸ â£
â£
De aardbol, waarop we leven begint flink toegetakeld te worden. Het begint zijn sporen achter te laten. Zo beginnen we al een toename te zien van steeds meer frequente/extreme weer-omstandigheden die desastreuze gevolgen hebben.ğŸŒªï¸â£
â£
Meer dan 700 miljoen mensen hebben geen toegang tot schoon water.ğŸ’§â£
We hebben al 27% van onze koraalriffen verwoest, waar er maar liefst 25% van ons zeeleven leeft. ğŸ³â£
Er worden 160.000 plastic zakken per seconde gebruikt. Plastic breekt amper tot niet af! âŒâ£
â£
Tegen het jaar 2030 hebben we misschien maar 10% van de regenwouden over en kan het over 100 jaar verdwenen zijnâ—â£
Door ontbossing kunnen in de komende 25 jaar 28.000 diersoorten uitsterven. ğŸ…â£
â£
We zullen geen welvarende, stabiele en rechtvaardige toekomst voor de mensheid bouwen op een gedegradeerde planeet. Het milieu beschermen naast economische en sociale ontwikkeling is van cruciaal belang voor ons wel zijn. Beter produceren en verstandiger consumeren is de sleutel tot het stand brengen van het beschermen van natuurlijke rijkdom en bijdragen aan het algehele economische en sociale welzijn. â™»ï¸â£
â£
Door dit allemaal achterwege te houden, hebben 2 jongens uit een kleine stad in Twente van 19 jaar het initiatief genomen te gaan ondernemen op een maatschappelijk verantwoorde manier door een platform te creÃ«ren, waarop het hoofd concept gericht is op eco-vriendelijke artikelen, waarbij we op lange termijn een grote impact willen hebben op de samenleving. ğŸŒâ£
â£
Dit door een platform te beginnen, waarop we ons richten op â€˜eco-vriendelijke productenâ€™. Zo geloven we er heilig in dat we met onze platform een impact kunnen maken op de koopbehoefte van de algemene klant, om zo een groot mogelijk steentje bij te dragen aan de maatschappij! â™»ï¸â€¼ï¸

bio: meditationğŸ™ #yoga #shamanismğŸ¦‹ #vegetarianğŸŒ¾ğŸ“¿ Yoga philosophy made easyYoga Teacher-500h YTTLike what you read? Give backğŸ¤²  DE38100110012629166573
post_1_content:
_roots_of_joy_
Trusting the process, divine timing and Mercury retrograding.

To trust the process means to be reminded of how little our daily problems may look on the overall. Moreover, they may be blessings in disguise.

Remember to always see the big picture, to trust divine timing. Things might seems shity right now or uncertain because of the Covid situation. And no we have no visibilty, the veil of certainty is gone, and now we get to see how life really always was : a mistery.

Trusting the process means to trust divine timing, to decide to trust rather than doubt. That for example things you did that seemed irrational or dumb right now, might in fact be exactly what needed to happen.

I woke up on the 4th of January at 4:44am to book the cheapest possible flight to Costa Rica, now my flight has been cancelled and I could of course fall into the trap of doubting all of my decisions that led to this present uncertain moment.

But had I not booked this flight that very day I would probably not have had the guts to quit the unhappy job I was in. And today my life would look completely different, and obviously worse than it is now.

Sometimes, things get mixed up, messed up, you send a text to the wrong person, book a flight a the wrong (or is it) date (just happened to me today), miss an important meeting, you "don't arrive on time". Mercury is retrograding today, and you know what we say: beware for that is the moment all electronics/messages get messed/mixed up. Be careful of what you say and how you say it etc.

Mercury represents is the messenger of the Gods, what if those moments during this phase when things get out of hands are in fact : "divine timing" like a freudian labsus your soul just can't control.

You blurt out what was hidden, what you actually wanted to say or do for a long time but were not admitting to yourself.
You let the unconscious take the lead for a while, you accept these weird events happening that for now seem and feel unpleasant, but remember, when you dream, you have no control (unless you are lucid dreaming but that is for another post) sometimes you have a nightmare sometimes you have the best dream ever and sometimes a revelation.
1d
post_2_content:
_roots_of_joy_
There is a gateway to serenity and inner peace : bhakti Yoga. The path of devotion.

So what does it mean to be devoted? And to what or whom should we be devoted?

All religion and philosophies point up to the sky and right back at you for what goes up must come down (alchemists in the room you see what I just did there^^) to our inner God.

Look at it this way: we are born helpless and have to look outward for shelter, safety, food and love.

We make our parents are gods. Then we grow up, realize they are just humans and get really angry and sad at them for having (maybe badly) fucked up our illusion.

Some of us find comfort in religion on the way of healing, others find refuge in the security of science and litterature.

Whatever medicine you choose to soothe your inner fear and insecurities with, its all the same in the end.

As long as you do not trust in your own inner creative fire, your inner power, you will keep give your power away to others or misuse it against them to reassure your ego.

So what bhakti Yoga really means is, to honor Thyself as you would honor and respect your God.

Maybe you were never loved by your parents, it is very sad, but it happens, and surely they themselves did not know how to love and have never received it.

But you can break this karmic cycle. You can trust that something bigger than you loves you and has your back. You can name it God, Nature, Source of Life, the Universe, or invoque any author/philosopher that resonates with your beliefs. Whatever you name it, if this belief gives you strenght, and leaves you feeling loved and complete, keep going for you have found the door to Bhakti Yoga.

Once you realize that nobody has power over you and that in exchange you do not have any power (or right to have!) on anybody, you are free to be and can start weaving bonds of love instead.

We are all seeking, and we will all find a gateway, a door only we have the key to open. In this life or in the other (if you find the reference, please comment)

I wish you all a peacefull evening. May your sorrow be alleviated from your hearts, tomorow is another day and each morning we are born again.

Namaste
3d
post_3_content:
_roots_of_joy_
What do you see in this picture?

Well your future.

Your future body, your future cells.
What you eat will soon be a part of you.

There is a saying from Thich Nhat Hanh in his wonderful book "Anger" in which he writes "Eat happy eggs from happy chickens". He writes that when you eat the meat of angry chickens, you eat their anger as well.

I strongly recommend you his book which has helped me in many ways. But this special passage at the beginning of the book struck me by its wisdom and simplicity (as I am on holidays I do not have the book with me at the moment but uploaded a capture of the book in my stories). As you can see he is not advocating for vegetarianism but rather for non violence. For violence leads to anger and unprocessed anger to resentment and more violence : never ending circle.

In the philosophy of Yoga this is what we call "ahimsa" "non-violence". That is the reason why most Yogis are vegeterian or vegan.

Because unfortunately the way most animals on the planet are tortured in order to be eaten.

But the same goes for the vegetables as well: how where yout veggies planted and grown and reaped? Was there suffering in the process?
The same goes for our clothes, the objects we buy, the words we pronounce, the pictures we put online , the media we consume.... My point here is not to guilt trip anyone, but to point out how much suffering there is in this world. To empower us to become aware of it in order to change it.

You do not need to feel guilty if you are a meat eater or if you buy your clothes at fast fashion shops, for guilt is a uselss emotion, like shame is.
Rather, like in your meditation practice, notice, take time to notice and to question, to seek information and to ask for answers and practical solutions.

The world is very complex and no one can tell you how to live your life and nobody has it "all figured out". We are in this together and small actions have impact, just your awareness, you reading this post has impact.

Like the DalaÃ¯-lama said "if you think you are too small to make a difference, try to sleeping with a mosquito." Namaste

It's not Black vs White
It's literally all good people vs racists

And we all pick a team through our actions.
3d
post_3_content:
kluebeats
After a week that has been incredibly challenging emotionally and psychologically, seeing what's happening to our brothers and sisters in the US, I can't describe how grateful I am to have had the experience that the rally in Sydney was yesterday.  To see that there are so many people, from all walks of life who care about humanity enough to defy the initial (clearly bullshit, eventually overturned) legal directives to come together in solidarity to mourn the death of George Floyd and too many others, to show support for the Black Lives Matter movement, to oppose the unjust and violent Policing that continues kill Indigenous people in custody, and to stand against systematic racism that affects people of colour everywhere.

What I saw yesterday made me so proud of my city, and gives me hope for the future.
Thank you.

Happy 30.000km anniversary for my beautiful road bike @planetxbikes ğŸ˜

Vandaag tijdens een rustig ritje de 30.000e kilometer op mijn 'nieuwe' fiets gereden!! Ik heb al zoveel mooie ritten gemaakt op deze fiets; zonnige zomersritten, maar ook winterse trainingsritten door de vrieskou, een heleboel bergen beklommen, gravelpaadjes ontdekt, extreem lange ritten gemaakt, (team)tijdritten mee gereden (en gewonnen), en ongeveer elke heuvel in Nederland mee bedwongen.

post_2_content:
mirandacycling
Crazy weather, busy day and a nice rideğŸ˜Š

Vanochtend er van overtuigd de wekker op snooze gedrukt te hebben, maar dat bleek niet zo toen ik een half uur later wakker werdğŸ˜…

Gelukkig neem ik meestal sochtends de tijd om lekker rustig aan te doen, dus was ik nu met opschieten ruim op tijd op werk. Sinds deze week sta ik weer voor de klas, heerlijk maar ook druk. Op de terugweg enorme regenbuien tegengekomen waardoor de straten zelfs even blank stonden.

Bij thuiskomst stond er nog een core training en rondje fietsen op de planning, dat werd dus zweten in het tacxhok.

Terwijl ik aan mijn core training begon trokken de wolken weg, en een half uur later was het droog.. toch maar buiten rijden? Buienradar liet mij weten dat ik daar iets meer dan een uur voor had. Dus ik ben snel op de fiets gesprongen. Het was een heerlijk ritje!

Van boven hield ik het droog, het wegdek daarentegen ğŸ˜…

#fietseninderegen #natwegdek #wielerleven #wielrennen #avondrit #coreworkout #planetxbikes #planetx @planetxbikes #cyclinglife #cyclinglove #cycling #cyclist #lovemyroadbike #lovetocycle #lovemybike #lovemyroadbike #lovetoride #alwayscycling #alwayshappyonthebike #cyclingintherain
2d
post_3_content:
mirandacycling
Yesterday's rideğŸ˜Š

Vandaag nog een beetje nagenoten van de rit van gisteren. Heerlijk van die ritjes waardoor het voelt alsof je op vakantie bent. Vandaag voor het eerst sinds de corona uitbraak in Nederland weer voor de klas gestaan. En na zo'n lekker weekend, kon ik heerlijk aan de week beginnen.

Vandaag qua training even rustdag, morgen mag ik weer!

Ondanks dat (volgens mij) het advies van de @teamknwu is om met max 4 te fietsen, zie ik steeds meer grote groepen fietsen, en ook onbekende die elkaar tegenkomen en bij elkaar (of bij ons) in het wiel blijven plakken. Waar ik het normaal gesproken altijd heel leuk vond als iemand in het wiel kwam (rijden wij zo hard dat je mee wil liftenğŸ˜ğŸ’ª) was ik toen corona net in Nederland was er niet zo van gediend (en sprak wielplakkers er ook op aan; wil je vanwege corona even niet meeliften, de meeste begrepen dat wel). Momenteel weet ik niet zo goed wat ik moet doen. De maatregelen versoepelen, er mag weer in kleine groepjes gefietst worden. Maar of dan bij een vreemde in het wiel zo handig is, ik vind dat lastig inschatten.

Wat doe jij momenteel, nog steeds solo of alweer met bekende, of ook onbekende? En hoe vind je het als iemand bij jou in het wiel komt plakken momenteel?

post_1_content:
helen_flo
Corona Virus or Survivor's Guilt
It took me some time to find the words to describe the current situation. You're probably tired of all this talks, messages, pictures and videos about Corona, but I really want to comment on it.

The reason for it is an optimistic police report, that was published yesterday in some article. I don't know where and how they gathered data and wrote something like "people understand how serious it is...". What I see (almost every day), less and less people take it seriously. More and more people not wearing mask properly (or not wearing at all). Another reason for my post is an encounter with guy, who didn't wear a mask (but he had one around his neck) while shopping with his parents, because he was freed of it (some medical issues whatsoever). I asked him to put his mask on his face, the reply was "I'm freed, should I show you my medical certificate?" I was ready to explode! Does he really think his paper will save him from the virus? What about his parents? The guy wasn't helping them while shopping anyway, what's the point of having him there??? I do understand it's hot in a mask, you can't breathe and so on and so on... BUT you need to wear a mask for 20-30 Minutes, while shopping, people who work in the shop have to wear it for 4-8 hours!!! If you don't care about the virus, at least have some RESPECT for someone who works, so you can buy your noodles and toilet paper!!! Same works for public transport: is it so hard to wear a mask on the train? You won't suffocate, don't worry.

The last, but not least, the quote "I don't know anyone, who has the virus". YOU'RE LUCKY! (just for you to know) it does NOT mean it is not there. One thing is to know someone who has it, another one is to lose someone because of it.
Be mindful!!! Take all the measures (wash hands, wear a mask, social distancing) to keep yourself and, what is even more important, other people safe! By doing simple actions, you might safe someone's life even without knowing it.
P.S. I know most of you, who will read it till the end, are mindful and behave accordingly. Maybe it will motivate you to keep it up and spread the word to others ğŸ˜‰

This photo sums up how I feel on World Oceans Day today: treading uncharted waters, trying to stay afloat, head barely above the surface.

Thereâ€™s a lot going on in the world right now. In isolation they are m a s s i v e issues - climate breakdown, social injustice, global welfare - but when grappling them collectively (and we should because they are all interlinked) it can be mentally overwhelming and exhausting.

But if we really want to change the world then dipping our toes in and splashing around in the shallows isnâ€™t enough. Weâ€™ve got to dive into the depths of uncharted territories to push boundaries.

And we also have to recognise when itâ€™s time to get to ashore to catch our breath and rest.

I know a lot of people are feeling overwhelmed and exhausted right now. Thatâ€™s because youâ€™re in the deep end and itâ€™s demanding stamina because your feet canâ€™t touch the ground - but treading water doesnâ€™t get you any further. It just stops you sinking.

Go back to shore and give yourself a break. You need to keep up strength if you want to go the distance.

Photo by @benduffyphoto.

Attachment system lesson number 2. (Let me know if you like these in the comments ğŸ™) People often associate feelings of love with an activated attachment system. What does that mean? When people encounter threats (a partner not texting back, someone pulling away, someone becoming emotionally distant), their attachment systems are activated and they become motivated to seek closeness from this person. The person becomes preoccupied and often obsessed with the person who has pulled away. This feeling is often confused with love. People with an anxious attachment style have a much more easily activated attachment system. And because they often date people with an avoidant attachment style, the feeling of â€œdangerâ€ or â€œdistanceâ€ happens much more often.
This also means when an anxious person meets someone with a secure attachment system - someone who is an open communicator and ready to love them. They often perceive these potential partners as boring and having â€œno sparkâ€

Get yourself a copy of the book Attached! By Amir Levine and Rachel S. F. Heller

One less piece of plastic to worry about.. oh, hang on.. I'm talking about the sports shirt! ğŸ˜³ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£
.
Ok.. disclaimer time.. I am not sponsored by @ironrootsathletics or receive any money etc.. but I did receive this shirt from them.
.
But i was very excited about it.. and still am after this evening's run!
.
I don't know if other vegans have this issue but sometimes I feel I have to make eco compromises.. such as using synthetic fibres.. especially when it comes to my sports gear.
.
So when I saw this Dutch based company (3 young guys I think) start making sports wear from #tencel .. my ears pricked up.
.
Go to @ironrootsathletics website to find out more.. basically it is made from renewable eucalyptus and hemp.
.
Oh lordy.. this all sounds like a bluddy advert huh?.. it isn't meant to be but I wanna talk about it as I am genuinely excited.. why?.. because it isn't made from synthetics, so no micro plastics are coming off this shirt and into the water system. .
I won't comment on how it performs yet, because 1 run isn't enough.. but I will keep you posted.
Initial impressions though? Love it. Feels like something you can do your sports in and then carry on wearing afterwards at the beach. .
If you have any questions about this then feel free to ask away. As always the important thing for me is honesty and integrity.. so ask the hard questions.
.
That is actually why I post photos that I take on the day.. you will see exactly how often I use any specific item.
.
Finally.. even though I am over 50 with wobbly bits, I wanted to try and take a beefcake model photo.. see photo 2.. did I succeed? HahağŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£
.
.
Oooh.. and two bags of trash collected from a bag I found so that is 2 bags I suppose for @just1bag2020 #just1bag2020 .
.

post_2_content:
wayeoflife
â€œDo you ever plan these plogs, come back the next day, and all the trash is gone?â€
.
That was a question my brooks #runhappy teammate @emmekeschalken asked me last night.
.
She had seen a story I posted, saying that I had found a lot of litter by a bench but couldnâ€™t pick it up at that time, so I planned on coming back the next day to get it.
.
The film I made is of me returning to the spot 12hrs later.
.
Yep. The litter was still there.. but that isn't the full story.
.
There was also another location on yesterday's run that I had spotted trash and decided I would collect today.
An empty plastic bottle.
.
It is near the start/end of my run so I decided to get it on the return leg (an hour later)
But when I went past it this morning on the first time, I noticed the other thing that can happen.. more litter had appeared. .
The bottle had attracted someone else's litter since last night. #trashattractstrash .
.
Oh well.. more to collect at the end of the run... Except.. when I can back an hour later.. it had all gone!!
.
A fellow plogger or litter collector must have collected it while I was on my loop.
.
That is a good day.
That is something that makes me super happy
.
So.. to answer Emmeke's question.. Yes, sometimes it isn't there when I return.
And when it is gone.. it is a great day.
.
I am also trying something new out today. I have also put this on YouTube (link to my YouTube channel in my profile).. but rather than just put the same thing on there, I have put a little monologue on at the end.. let me know if you think it is cool!
.
.
.

Multitasking is such a big talent when you are in Medicine!
I never really thought of how many things I actually do in a day but itâ€™s a lot. I am currently studying three different topics, I have two assignments that are due end of June and I also have classes and work! I have meetings and I am also trying to keep up with my Insta.
In general it is a lot in a day but I am so used to this pace and my hectic schedule that at the end of the day I am not bothered by it!
I think what drives me the most to succeed are my goals and the fact that I know that this hectic schedule is not gonna be here forever! Vacation is coming soon and I am holding onto that thought to pull me through this last month of studying.
Tips for keeping up with exams and finals and multitasking: âœ¨Set daily goals and to do lists âœ¨Focus and avoid distractions âœ¨Always make schedules and plan as you go. If something doesnâ€™t work change it until it does!
âœ¨Eat well and sleep for at least 8 hours a day.
âœ¨Exercise, I personally exercise three times a week and it really helps me with concentration.
âœ¨Take small breaks and walk.
âœ¨Change yo the subjects you are studying so if you have to study multiple ones just spread them through the week and have a variety of topics in a day!
âœ¨Donâ€™t let others distract you.
âœ¨Use resources that you like to study from, so for example you can buy a textbook you always wanted to buy or watch the videos that you enjoy.
âœ¨It takes time and effort to succeed, always remember that!

Deze periode staat in het teken van Black Lives Matters en de protesten waarin wordt opgeroepen tot gelijkheid. De aandacht voor discriminatie en racisme blijft toenemen en dat is maar goed ook. De gesprekken over deze problemen blijken moeizaam en ingewikkeld, maar ze moeten gevoerd worden. Ook wij verdiepen ons in de onderwerpen en dan met name op de lange geschiedenis waarin de problemen zijn ontstaan. Als historici denken wij - hoe clichÃ© misschien ook - dat het nodig is om het verleden te kennen om het heden te begrijpen. En dan niet alleen met een kritische blik naar Amerika, maar juist (ook) gericht op Nederland.â£
â£
Een van de geschiedenissen die vandaag de dag veel besproken wordt is het Nederlandse bewind in Suriname. Om je hier in te verdiepen is het boek van Anton de Kom, Wij slaven van Suriname, een 'must' om te lezen. Anton de Kom, een afstammeling van tot slaafgemaakten schreef dit boek in 1934. Hij vertelt hoe de Nederlanders het land en zijn inwoners onderdrukte. Hij vertelt over de mensonterende praktijken op de plantages en maakt pijnlijk duidelijk wat de erfenis van het koloniale verleden van Nederland inhoudt. En extra bijzonder: hoewel het boek in 1934 is geschreven, is het (helaas) steeds ontzettend relevant.â£
â£

goeieouwekoeien
Museuminhaalslag 2/8 en alvast een tip voor aankomend weekend: het Zuiderzeemuseum in Enkhuizen. Ja Roos staat hier in een museum! Een compleet dorp, dat bestaat uit 140 historische gebouwen die uit verschillende dorpen rond de voormalige Zuiderzee zijn verplaatst naar deze plek. Sommigen in zijn geheel, anderen steen voor steen. Over de weg of per boot. Bizar toch!â£
â£
In 1932 werd de Afsluitdijk afgerond en veranderde het leven in de dorpen aan de Zuiderzee compleet. In het museum duik je in de wereld van de bewoners van het Zuiderzeegebied voor 1932. Je kan zelf ook van alles doen, beluisteren en bekijken. Het museum ligt prachtig aan het water. Een heerlijk dagje uit! âœ…â£
â£

Met welke ideeeÌˆn is de Bijlmer ooit ontworpen? Wat hebben de Nieuwmarktrellen te maken met de aanleg van de Bijlmer? Wat zegt de bouwstijl van de Bijlmer over de gedachten over wonen van toen? En waar komt de huidige reputatie van de Bijlmer vandaan? Dat en meer heeft Tim ons allemaal verteld. Dank voor de interessante rondleiding!

I have a question!

Some questions I was asked today:
A morning interview about the role of social corporate entrepreneurship in our education systems: how can educators locked in an old system be free to promote an entrepreneurial mindset in currently passive students?

With the B Lab Europe community: what kind of engagement would create a bigger SDG impact, going deep with a few key companies or go wide with breadth of diversity?
What are the ideal elements of a summit bringing together people from companies around Europe virtually?

Whatâ€™s for lunch? from my youngest son

ebbf conversation: how do I find people who give me clarity about my purpose? why does this organization give me energy? what makes it so attractive?

How can we create a manifesto for action, that will drive government incentives for companies that contribute most to society?

How can we best bring together books, articles, podcastsproduced by a global community of members and make it easy for pioneers to find what is relevant to them?

In the evening: how do we find people in other companies who fit with our culture?
how can you become a complex learner in a complex learning organization in a complex learning society?

what is life?
a gift?
a journey?
a market?
an art?

Do you have any answers (or good questions) for me?

taschaskeuken
Move over Dalgona coffee, focaccia art is here! Focaccia flower patches made with vegetables and herbs seem to be the new craze.
This sourdough focaccia recipe is a great starting point if youâ€™re not yet a confident sourdough bread baker as it does not require any complicated techniques and uses some instant yeast as well to ensure a light and airy result.
It can be topped with any type of vegetables or herbs as long as the cook time of the veg does not exceed 30 mins at 200 C

Use sheet tray of 15 x 25 cm or slightly larger.

For the dough:
Â· 250 grams ripe sourdough starter
Â· 250 grams lukewarm water
Â· 540 grams white bread flour
Â· 55 grams melted Flora Plant or other plant-based margarine
Â· 12 grams salt
Â· 30 grams maple syrup (or honey if not vegan)
Â· 7 grams instant yeast

For the toppings + sheet tray:
Â· Vegetables and herbs Â· 2 tablespoons olive oil + extra for drizzling
Â· Flaky sea salt
Â· Parchment optional

Method:
Â· Combine all dough ingredients and knead by hand (15 mins) or by stand mixer (7-10 mins)
Â· Place dough in an olive oil coated bowl + drizzle some on oil on top. Cover and let rise at room temp until doubled (depending on weather 30-60 minutes).
Â· Once doubled, knock back and fold onto itself 6 times. Cover and let rise for another 60 mins.
Â· Drizzle tray w/ 2 tbsp olive oil. Optionally line w/ parchment paper for easy release. Turn your dough out onto tray. Roll through oil, gently press outwards to stretch and fit to sheet tray.
Â· Cover sheet tray and ferment in fridge for 12-16 hours.
Â· â€ªRemove tray from fridge while oven preheats to 200 C for 30 mins.â€¬
Â· Gently dimple the dough. Top with veggies and herbs and sprinkle w/ flaky sea salt. Drizzle w/ olive oil.
Â· Bake 20-30 minutes until golden brown #brood #focaccia #focacciaart #sourdoughstarter #zuurdesemstarter #rotterdam #rotterdamfood #bread #brood #sourdough #sourdoughfocaccia #focacciaflower #masamadre #desembrood #zuurdesem #fermentation #bakmedanalsjekan #coronabaking #igzuurdesem #igzuurdesem #Upfielders #upfieldbakes

How do you like to eat white asparagus?

The crust is puff pastry, I added two cloves of garlic to 100 grams of spreadable goats cheese for the base. For the topping I grilled the asparagus, chopped half a red onion and instead of the suggested boiled egg I used oven dried tomatoes (recipe by @anniepannie_nl). To finish I added some basil and chives and as I didnâ€™t have any fresh ones I added dried edible flowers.

Last sunday I joined @tantealighieri on a 6h hike. We started at Oberalppass (canton of Uri) and went up to the 2740 m Pazolastock, which was mostly still covered in snow.
From there on we continued on steep ridges and got to the magical frozen Lej da Tuma (canton of Grison) and saw the Rhine source which leads 1300 km downstream to its sea mounting in Rotterdam (NL). One of the more challenging hikes but defo one for the books!

Deze hashtag heb ik al eerder gebruikt. Het is een afkorting voor Not On Planet Earth. Het staat voor alles wat we niet op deze planeet willen.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Voor mij is duurzaam leven zowel kijken naar planeet als mens. Het gaat samen. Beter zorgen voor beiden creÃ«ert een duurzame wereld waar we in symbiose leven met elkaar.

post_3_content:
sustain.abilities_
Overshoot Day ğŸŒ

Duurzaam leven betekent voor mij ook educatie. De werking van de planeet en de verschillende ecosystemen zijn immens complex, maar daardoor zoveel interessanter.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Het zorgt er ook voor dat ik blijf onthouden waarom ik duurzamer wil leven en het versterkt mijn motivatie, mijn doorzettingsvermogen en zelfs mijn activistisch kantje.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Daarom wil ik het even hebben over Overshoot Day. Het is de dag dat we alle resources van de aarde hebben opgebruikt die we dat jaar mogen gebruiken. Daarna spreken we dus eigenlijk reserves aan.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
In 1970 was Overshoot Day op 29 december en is al jaren aan het opschuiven. Dit jaar zal ze vallen op 22 augustus. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Wetenschappers maken ook berekeningen per land omdat er hierbij toch grote verschillen zijn. BelgiÃ« is misschien een klein land, maar we hebben een grote ecologische voetafdruk. Onze Overshoot Day is al gevallen, 5 april. Niet goed bezig dus.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Wil je meer weten over deze dag? Op @earthovershootday en op de website kan je meer informatie vinden. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Probeer dus duurzamer te leven en minder grondstoffen te gebruiken. Zo zetten we samen een stap richting een duurzamere wereld ğŸŒ¿

Thank you @mountyflower_ and @keros.ene for coming along and letting me photography them in awkward situations with the masks on. I know itâ€™s hard but you guys rocked it! -

In this #PhotoShoot video Iâ€™ll show you how I approach a #conceptual shoot. The main #idea of this photo session is to show and emphasize the toxic society in which weâ€™re living. Of course, #Covid19 and the whole quarantine situation helped in shaping this idea, this image in my head, but itâ€™s not supposed to be about the quarantine. Itâ€™s not about the physical toxicity itâ€™s about the toxicity of people, things, everything that surrounds us really, to the point where you have to filter everything therefore, the gas mask. IngrediÃ«nten:

Werkwijze:
- klop de zachte boter met de suiker tot een crÃ¨me
- splits de eieren en roer de dooiers een voor een door het boter-suikermengsel
- voeg bloem, gistpoeder, zetmeel en noten toe

- laat de taart afkoelen in de vorm
- maak het glazuur en besmeer de afgekoelde en ontvormde taart ermee (ik deed enkel op de bovenkant glazuur zodat de nootjes aan de zijkant zichtbaar blijven)

Throughout the last 7 years my mental health was always something that I disregarded and blatantly ignored; mostly due to the fact I didnâ€™t want to face the consequences of stigma and judgement that those with mental illness get labeled with daily. Iâ€™ve seen the extremely devastating effects that it has had on my relationships and loved ones, which has resulted in complicated friendships and cutting off others from my life; in other areas it has effected my grades, the way I viewed others, and ultimately the way I viewed myself. I have been in multiple â€lowsâ€ where my mental health was strained so intensely and I was in a dire need of help where I honestly fully considered something as scary as suicide. Yet, despite this, I continued to take on new challenges and continually said yes to those who needed me because I felt it was the only way to validate that I was still needed. Itâ€™s only now as I go through some life-changing events such as LIGHThouse that I realize those lows made me who I am today. Iâ€™m proud to have fought and continue fighting my mental illness while also promoting mental health â€” mental illness does NOT define who I am. But I will forever be affected by its presence in my life. Im so lucky to have my family and close friends who I appreciate so much for helping me through everything and giving me unconditional love, no matter how hard I had been on myself. Iâ€™m in a point of my life that I am the happiest Iâ€™ve ever been and my brain feels so focused on continuing to see how far I can get in life. Iâ€™m so happy to share that with all of you.
Let me know if you need anything ..

Please read this poem by @dichtwater by swiping all the way through - and let's ask ourselves why #sorryindutch
These sentences will stay with me forever *
'...omdat we weigeren te erkennen dat er iets niet klopt
zoals de harten van George Floyd, Mitch Henriquez, Michael Brown en Eric Garner ook niet kloppen'
and so many others #saytheirnames *
'waarom haten we, doen we slecht?
waarom noemen we iets het recht?
als het system zo krom is
dat het niet voor elk mens even hard vecht' *
'waarom verstoppen we ons achter
"ik ben geen racist"
het gaat niet over jou
het gaat over een systeem waarin gelijkheid in kansen en rechten structureel mist' *
'...sta stil en spreek je uit
niet om je gelijk te krijgen
maar om iedereen gelijk te krijgen'

Now let's keep on fighting and make this happen.

#blacklivesmatter #blacklivesmatternl #blm #dichtwater #educateyourself #whiteprivilege
#makeithappen #stopracism @kozwartepiet @nederlandwordtbeter @akwasion

post_3_content:
mariekeeyskoot
Gosh, I miss this... Clearly there is a lot going on in the world at the moment that is way more significant than being able to stand on a stage. And yet. Going on a journey of gained insights and heightened experience together. Getting to sense each other's response to one-liners, statistics or music. Feeling part of a crowd, of a gathering, of a movement. So special.
And being the one connecting it all, content and people - ensuring everyone is part of the pack, no-one is left behind. Sharing your story, making someone laugh, inspiring a change of pace, of choice, of behaviour. Magic.

I love being a presenter, a host, a keynote speaker. And I cannot wait to be back! This was me on stage at the Embassy of The Netherlands in Brussels, last year. Slowly, slowly it's starting up - for the first time in months I'm being approached again to present and speak. In the meantime I've had the pleasure to host a few online events, and to organise and participate in IG lives. I've always wanted to be a television presenter ;) so please don't hesitate to contact me for any virtual event you're creating. Hope to see many of you again soon, somewhere, somehow. Massive hug x M

Pic by Daphne Molendijk / Dutch Embassy Brussels

I read this book about 15 years ago for the first time. I didnâ€™t like reading at the time but a friend suggested it. I liked it and it made some sort of impact on me. But it was more or less just a â€˜storyâ€™ to me. I was 14 or 15 and didnâ€™t really bother to understand why this book was different than the other books I read at that time. Then again, I didnâ€™t read much at the time.
Now I am re-reading it with a completely different perspective, different knowledge and an understanding as to what this book is and means. In the past years Iâ€™ve come to love reading and read many books that were new to me fiction and non-fiction. Among them were books about racism, (racial) injustice, discrimination and inequality because itâ€™s important to know about (our) history, about whatâ€™s going on in the world now and to listen to others who might show you a different perspective on subjects that you thought you had your mind made up anout or come with new information that changes things for you. And in general I donâ€™t read books twice. However, I felt I had to re-read this book and read the words again. But carefully this time. This is a book that everyone should read. Or re-read for that matter.
I am halfway through and if anyone wants to borrow it when I am finished let me know.
